Week 3 – Data Cleaning & Preprocessing (Power BI)
Objective
Clean and preprocess dataset using Power BI Power Query.
In week 3, the dataset was cleaned using Power BI Power Query. Missing values were identified and handled. Unnecessary columns were removed and column names were standardized.
Data types were corrected and duplicate records were checked. This step ensured that the dataset became suitable for further analysis and visualization. 
Day-wise Activities

Day 1 – Importing Dataset
Imported dataset into Power BI
Connected data source
Reviewed table preview

Day 2 – Handling Missing Values
Used Power Query tools
Replaced null values
Removed unnecessary rows

Day 3 – Removing Irrelevant Columns
Deleted unused columns
Renamed columns properly
Improved dataset readability

Day 4 – Data Type Correction
Converted:
Date fields
Numeric columns
Text fields
Verified consistency

Day 5 – Duplicate Validation
Checked duplicate entries
Applied filtering rules
Loaded cleaned dataset into Power BI model

Outcome
Dataset optimized for visualization
Clean and structured data model
